  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-7229">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/p5wSqJO-bIc?si=_-SM0CzDAFnIRrEm" target="_blank"
        >Be Prepared (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-7229 mb-requirement-id-7230">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the hazards you are most likely to
        encounter while using leatherwork tools and materials, and what you
        should do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, or lessen these
        hazards.<br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/eDDvWMyOPO8?si=svFeILuCoVTRbjng"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety in Leatherwork | Dangers and Health and Safety Tips (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-7229 mb-requirement-id-7231">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could
        occur while working with leather, including minor cuts and scratches,
        puncture wounds, ingested poisoning, and reactions from exposure to
        chemicals such as dyes, cements, and finishes used in leatherworking.<br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Leatherwork/Leatherwork_First%20Aid.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.aad.org/public/everyday-care/injured-skin/burns/treat-minor-cuts"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Minor Cuts (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/first-aid/first-aid-puncture-wounds/basics/art-20056665"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Puncture Wounds (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
